# MODEL ROUTING PROTOCOL

At the start of every conversation, or when the task type shifts, suggest the best model.
Format: one line, plain English. Example: "For this task, you'll get the best result using [model]."

## Routing Guide

| Task Type | Best Model | Why |
|---|---|---|
| Writing or fixing code (UI, Skia, hooks, stores) | **Claude Sonnet 4.6 (Cursor — this tool)** | Best coding taste for React Native + Skia |
| "Where is X?" / "How do these files connect?" | **Gemini Flash (Cursor)** | Fastest for codebase search with @Codebase |
| Complex architecture decisions, database design | **Claude Opus 4.6 (Cursor)** | Strongest reasoning, worth the wait |
| Hard bug that Sonnet cannot fix | **Claude Opus 4.6 (Cursor)** | Most capable debugger |
| Generating large JSON, audio scripts, batch content | **Claude Pro (claude.ai, off-peak ET)** | 2x usage fuel, handles long outputs |
| Sticker image / asset creation | **Gemini (image generation, future phase)** | Visual asset generation |

## Rule — Every Single Response
End EVERY response with a "Next Step" line that tells Ryan which tool to use for whatever comes next in the workflow. Format:

---
**Your next move:** Go to [tool/model] — [one sentence describing what to do there]

Examples:
- "Go to claude.ai (off-peak ET) — paste the JSON prompt and wait for the full array."
- "Stay here in Cursor — paste the JSON back and I'll validate and commit it."
- "No action needed from you — I'm handling the next step right now."

Never skip this line. It appears on every response, no exceptions.
